{% extends "_layout.twig" %}

{% set title = "Links" %}
{% set slug = "links" %}

{% block content %}
{% include 'reference/_partials/_quick-nav.twig' %}

  <div class="bg-white--tint pad">
    <section class="site-container">
      <h2 data-bk-layout class="font-xxl font-thin">{{ title }}</h2>

      <div data-bk-layout="palm:9 hands:8 lap:7" class="rte">
        <p class="font-m">Similar to the Basekit layout attribute, links in Basekit are also applied using a data attribute: <code>data-bk-links</code>.</p>

        <p>This scoping to a data attribute allows simpler configuration and less stuff in the class attribute.</p>
      </div>

      {% include "reference/_partials/_status.twig" with { value : 60 } %}

    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-white pad">
    <section class="site-container">
      <h3 data-bk-layout="pad:trl" class="font-l">Links styles</h3>

      <div data-bk-layout="hands:8 lap:7">
        <p>By default links are available in two main styles; primary and secondary. There are then various “modifiers” that can be applied to fine-tune link styles to suit their context.</p>

        <h3 class="font-bold pad-t">Undefined</h3>

        <div data-bk-links="">
          <p><a href="./">This link has no styles set</a> which makes it fairly useless but you can see there is no “default”, you have to make a choice.</p>
          <p class="font-s margin-t">Usage <code>data-bk-links=<strong>""</strong></code></p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-bold pad-l-t">Primary</h3>

        <div data-bk-links="primary">
          <p><a href="./">This link has the primary style</a> and on hover you’ll see the secondary colour. No transitions or underlines.</p>
          <p class="font-s margin-t">Usage <code>data-bk-links="<strong>primary</strong>"</code></p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-bold pad-l-t">Secondary</h3>

        <div data-bk-links="secondary">
          <p><a href="./">This link has the secondary style</a> and on hover you’ll see the primary colour. No transitions or underlines.</p>
          <p class="font-s margin-t">Usage <code>data-bk-links="<strong>secondary</strong>"</code></p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-bold pad-l-t">Fade</h3>

        <div data-bk-links="primary fade">
          <p><a href="./">This link has the fade transition</a> between the primary and secondary state. It works for all states.</p>
          <p class="font-s margin-t">Usage <code>data-bk-links="primary <strong>fade</strong>"</code></p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-bold pad-l-t">Underline</h3>

        <div data-bk-links="primary fade underline">
          <p><a href="./">This link has an underline</a> and the fade transition.</p>
          <p class="font-s margin-t">Usage <code>data-bk-links="primary fade <strong>underline</strong>"</code></p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-bold pad-l-t">Underline Hover</h3>

        <div data-bk-links="primary fade underline-hover">
          <p><a href="./">This link has an underline on hover</a> and the fade transition.</p>
          <p class="font-s margin-t">Usage <code>data-bk-links="primary fade <strong>underline-hover</strong>"</code></p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-bold pad-l-t">Underline Initial</h3>

        <div data-bk-links="primary fade underline-initial">
          <p><a href="./">This link initially has an underline</a> and it disappears on hover.</p>
          <p class="font-s margin-t">Usage <code>data-bk-links="primary fade <strong>underline-initial</strong>"</code></p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-bold pad-l-t">Dim</h3>

        <div data-bk-links="primary fade dim">
          <p><a href="./">This link is dimmed</a> until you hover.</p>
          <p class="font-s margin-t">Usage <code>data-bk-links="primary fade <strong>dim</strong>"</code></p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-bold pad-l-t">Dark Background</h3>

        <div data-bk-links="white underline-hover fade" class="color-grey font-thin">
          <div data-bk-layout class="bg-secondary--darker">
            <p><a href="./">This is a white link on dark background</a>. Applying reliable color hover-states on dark background can be quite tricky unless the colour pallette has been designed specifically for this. For example, our <span data-bk-links="primary"><a href="./">primary</a></span> and <span data-bk-links="secondary"><a href="./">secondary</a></span> styles don't look so good, particularly for WCAG compliant contrast ratios.</p>

            <p class="font-s margin-t">Usage <code>data-bk-links="<strong>white</strong> underline-hover fade"</code></p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-bold pad-l-t">Dark Background Improved</h3>

        <div data-bk-links="white dim fade underline-hover" class="color-white font-thin">
          <div data-bk-layout class="bg-secondary--darker">
            <p><a href="./">This is a white link on dark background</a> dimmed and with the fade transtion. I find this is the best compromise of style and clarity.</p>

            <p class="font-s margin-t">Usage <code>data-bk-links="<strong>white dim</strong> fade underline-hover"</code></p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-bold pad-l-t">Inherit</h3>

        <div data-bk-links="inherit dim fade underline" class="color-secondary--dark">
          <div data-bk-layout class="bg-white--tint">
            <p><a href="./">This link has inherited its parent text colour</a>. When using inherit I find similar rules that apply to links on dark backgrounds also apply here.</p>

            <p class="font-s font-light margin-t">Usage <code>data-bk-links="<strong>inherit</strong> dim fade underline"</code></p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-bold pad-l-t">Big Text</h3>

        <div data-bk-links="primary fade underline-initial">
          <p>Underlines look quote nice on words with descenders…</p>

          <p class="font-l font-thin margin-t"><a href="./">Photography, for example.</a></p>

          <p class="font-s margin-t">Usage <code>data-bk-links="primary fade underline-initial"</code></p>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div data-bk-layout="hands:4 lap:4 lap:pr:1" class="pad-b">
        <div class="alert alert--simple font-s">
          <h4 class="font-n margin-b"><strong>Note for developers</strong></h4>

          <p>These link styles will <strong>not</strong> apply to button links, because that would be silly.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>


<div class="bg-white--tint pad">
  <section class="site-container">
    <h3 data-bk-layout="pad:trl" class="font-l">Link Features</h3>

    <div data-bk-layout="hands:8 lap:7">
      <p>Using the following modifiers we can add neat little features to certain links to encourage interaction.</p>

      <h3 class="font-bold pad-t">More</h3>

      <div data-bk-links="primary fade more">
        <p><a href="./">Read More</p>

        <p class="font-s margin-t">Usage <code>data-bk-links="primary fade <strong>more</strong>"</code> (this will apply to <em>all</em> child links)</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="font-bold pad-l-t">External Link</h3>

      <div data-bk-links="primary fade exit">
        <p><a href="http://google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Visit Google</p>

        <p class="font-s margin-t">Usage <code>data-bk-links="primary fade <strong>exit</strong>"</code> and <code> target="_blank"</code></p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="font-bold pad-l-t">Scroll Down</h3>

      <div data-bk-links="primary fade down">
        <p><a href="#footer">Go to footer</p>

        <p class="font-s margin-t">Usage <code>data-bk-links="primary fade <strong>down</strong>"</code> and <code>href="#footer"</code> on the link (doesn't have to be “footer” though)</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="font-bold pad-l-t">Scroll Up</h3>

      <div data-bk-links="primary fade up">
        <p><a href="#start">Go to start</p>

        <p class="font-s margin-t">Usage <code>data-bk-links="primary fade <strong>up</strong>"</code> and <code>href="#start"</code> on the link (doesn't have to be “start” though)</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="font-bold pad-l-t">Download</h3>

      <div data-bk-links="primary fade download">
        <p><a href="./" download>Download this file</p>

        <p class="font-s margin-t">Usage <code>data-bk-links="primary fade <strong>download</strong>"</code> and <code>download</code> attribute on the link</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div data-bk-layout="hands:4 lap:4 lap:pr:1" class="pad-b">
      <div class="alert alert--simple font-s" data-bk-links="primary fade underline-initial">
        <h4 class="font-n margin-b"><strong>Note for developers</strong></h4>

        <p>These link styles <strong>can</strong> be applied to <a href="../buttons/">button style links</a>, because that makes sense 😊</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  </section>
</div>
